item.title: Abattoir bungled outbreak, worker claims
item.description: A Melbourne meat processing plant – where 58 positive virus cases have been identified – waited a week to make COVID-19 testing mandatory after its first infection, it has been claimed.

item.title: Woman’s body left in bathtub for months
item.description: A man accused of murdering his ex-partner allegedly spent about six days living in her Melbourne unit months afterwards with the body still decomposing upstairs, a court has heard.

item.title: New clues in 22-year-old homicide
item.description: New information could provide “significant leads” into the reopened case of a 1998 house fire that killed a 13-year-old Sydney boy.

item.title: Lockdown lifted at four Victorian prisons
item.description: Lockdown has been lifted at four Victorian prions after inmates tested negative for coronavirus.

item.title: Shares rise despite Budget blowout
item.description: Australian shares ended higher on Thursday after the federal government revealed its budget had blown out by $85.8 billion.

item.title: NBA exec help Hawks land former Cav
item.description: Hawks coach Brian Goorjian has revealed how two-time NBA executive of the year now club owner Bryan Colangelo sealed the signature of former Cleveland forward Deng Adel.

item.title: 27 new Sydney suburbs not welcome in Qld
item.description: The Queensland Premier has declared the City of Fairfield in Sydney’s southwest a coronavirus hot spot.

item.title: ‘He didn’t care I said no’: Alleged rape victim
Man’s ‘cold, callous’ role in toolbox killings
item.description: A New Zealand man will serve 13 years in jail for his “cold, continuous and callous” role in the manslaughter and torture of two people.

item.title: Bullets confident of securing Patterson
item.description: Brisbane Bullets officials are quietly confident of fending off rivals the New Zealand Breakers to re-sign NBL First Team star Lamar Patterson, with the American swingman to announce his future in the coming weeks.
